{"title_page": "Obturator hernia", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Obturator hernia \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           = [[General surgery]]\n| synonyms        =  \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\nAn '''obturator hernia''' is a rare type of [[hernia]] of the [[pelvic floor]] in which pelvic or abdominal contents protrudes through the [[obturator foramen]]. Because of differences in anatomy, it is much more common in women, especially [[Gravidity and parity|multiparous]] and older women who have recently lost a lot of weight. The diagnosis is often made intraoperatively after presenting with [[bowel obstruction]].\n\nThe [[Howship\u2013Romberg sign]] is suggestive of an obturator hernia, exacerbated by thigh extension, medial rotation and abduction.<ref name=\"pmid15191874\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Yamashita K, Hayashi J, Tsunoda T |title=Howship-Romberg sign caused by an obturator hernia|journal=Am. J. Surg. |volume=187 |issue=6 |pages=775\u20136 |date=June 2004 |pmid=15191874 |doi=10.1016/j.amjsurg.2003.10.020 }}</ref>  It is characterized by lancilating pain in the medial thigh/obturator distribution, extending to the knee; caused by hernia compression of the obturator nerve.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = 29334\n| ICD10           = K45\n| ICD9            = {{ICD9|553.8}}\n| ICDO            = \n| OMIM            = \n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = article\n| eMedicineTopic  = 775630\n| MeshID          = D006553\n| SNOMED CT       = 60627008\n}}\n{{Digestive system diseases}}\n\n[[Category:Hernias]]\n\n\n{{disease-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Obturator hernia \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           = [[General surgery]]\n| synonyms        =  \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\nAn '''obturator hernia''' is a rare type of [[hernia]] of the [[pelvic floor]] in which pelvic or abdominal contents protrudes through the [[obturator foramen]]. Because of differences in anatomy, it is much more common in women, especially [[Gravidity and parity|multiparous]] and older women who have recently lost a lot of weight. The diagnosis is often made intraoperatively after presenting with [[bowel obstruction]].\n\nThe [[Howship\u2013Romberg sign]] is suggestive of an obturator hernia, exacerbated by thigh extension, medial rotation and abduction.<ref name=\"pmid15191874\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Yamashita K, Hayashi J, Tsunoda T |title=Howship-Romberg sign caused by an obturator hernia|journal=Am. J. Surg. |volume=187 |issue=6 |pages=775\u20136 |date=June 2004 |pmid=15191874 |doi=10.1016/j.amjsurg.2003.10.020 }}</ref>  It is characterized by lancilating pain in the medial thigh/obturator distribution, extending to the knee; caused by hernia compression of the obturator nerve.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|   DiseasesDB     = 29334 \n|   ICD10          = K45  \n|   ICD9           = {{ICD9|553.8}} \n|   ICDO           = \n|   OMIM           = \n|   MedlinePlus    = \n|   eMedicineSubj  = article \n|   eMedicineTopic = 775630 \n|   MeshID         = D006553 \n}}\n{{Digestive system diseases}}\n\n[[Category:Hernias]]\n\n\n{{disease-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dismanet", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding new medical resources.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obturator_hernia"}
{"title_page": "All Girls Are the Same", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 song by Juice Wrld}}\n{{citation style|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n|name=All Girls Are the Same\n|cover=Juice Wrld - All Girls Are the Same.jpg\n|type=single\n|artist=[[Juice Wrld]]\n|album=Nothings Different {{noitalic|and}} [[Goodbye & Good Riddance]]\n|released=April 13, 2018\n|format={{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n|genre=[[Emo rap]]\n|length=2:45\n|label={{hlist|Grade A|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]}}\n|writer={{hlist|[[Jarad Higgins]]|[[Nick Mira]]}}\n|producer=Nick Mira\n|year=2018\n|next_title=[[Lucid Dreams (Juice Wrld song)|Lucid Dreams]]\n|next_year=2018\n|misc={{External music video|{{YouTube|h3EJICKwITw|\"All Girls Are the Same\"}}}}}}\n\n\"'''All Girls Are the Same aka THE BEST SONG EVER BY THE BEST PERSON EVER'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Juice Wrld]]. It was officially released as the lead single from his debut studio album ''[[Goodbye & Good Riddance]]'' on April 13, 2018, after its music video premiered in February. Produced by [[Nick Mira]], the song debuted at number 92 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and peaked at number 41.<ref>{{Citation|title=Listen to \u201cAll Girls Are the Same\u201d by Juice WRLD|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/juice-wrld-all-girls-are-the-same/|language=en|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\nThe track concentrates on how women in Juice Wrld's past relationships have broken his heart with their lies, and that he drinks hard liquor to cope with his sadness.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lyrics/8463346/juice-wrld-all-girls-are-the-same-lyrics|title=Here Are the Lyrics to Juice WRLD's 'All Girls Are the Same'|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe official music video was directed by Cole Bennett, and was released on February 25, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/juice-wrld-drops-the-cole-bennett-directed-all-girls-are-the-same-new-video.43333.html|title=Juice WRLD Drops The Cole Bennett-Directed \"All Girls Are The Same\"|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2019-12-05}}</ref>\n\n== Remix ==\nThe official remix of the song features American rapper [[Lil Yachty]], who first previewed the collaboration on Instagram in late March 2018. Juice Wrld posted another snippet on Instagram on May 6.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/06/lil-yachty-juice-wrld-all-girls-are-the-same-remix/|title=Lil Yachty Joins Juice Wrld on \"All Girls Are the Same (Remix)\" - XXL|last=Miller|first=Kai|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref> On June 25, 2018, when Lil Yachty uploaded the song on [[SoundCloud]], it was immediately deleted due to copyright issues. However, fans managed to download the song before its removal, and it has since been available on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-yachty-jumps-on-juice-wrlds-all-girls-are-the-same-for-his-latest-remix-new-song.1979191.html|title=Lil Yachty Jumps On Juice WRLD's \"All Girls Are The Same\" For His Latest Remix|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2019-12-08}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018\u20132019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=\"ARIA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2019/12/aria-chart-watch-555/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #555|publisher=auspOp|date=December 14, 2019|accessdate=December 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| 98\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100|title=Canadian Music: Top 100 Songs Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| 54\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Sweden Heatseeker ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/215?dsp